Name: hypotrichosis 14
Definition: A hypotrichosis that is characterized by sparse to absent lanugo-like scalp hair
Synonym: multiple joint dislocations-short stature-craniofacial dysmorphism-congenital heart defects syndrome

Name: hypotrichosis 2
Definition: A hypotrichosis that has_material_basis_in a autosomal dominant mutation of CDSN on chromosome 6p21.33.

Name: hypotrichosis 3
Definition: A hypotrichosis that has_material_basis_in a autosomal dominant mutation of KRT74 on chromosome 12q13.13.

Name: hypotrichosis 4

Name: hypotrichosis 5

Name: hypotrichosis 6

Name: hypotrichosis 7

Name: hypotrichosis 9

Name: alopecia
Definition: A hypotrichosis that is characterized by a loss of hair from the head or body.
